name: 3-(boc-amino)-3-(3-methoxyphenyl)propionic acid

The structural modifications we need to consider are the presence of a methoxyphenyl group, which can increase the melting point due to the enhancement of the crystalline structure and the increase in molecular weight. Additionally, the amino group can participate in hydrogen bonding, which can also contribute to the melting point.
